iStock (iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - The South African military says rebels in eastern Democratic Republic of Congo have attacked a South African unit that is part of a United Nations peacekeeping mission, killing one soldier and injuring two others.The military says four rebels were killed and two were captured in the fighting on Monday morning near Butembu in DRC's Beni region.South Africa's statement says its soldiers repelled the rebel attack.The UN peacekeeping mission in eastern DRC includes a force intervention brigade with a mandate to take offensive military action against rebel groups.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.